@John, I'm glad you're enjoying the finger drumming techniques on the Arp! It really does add a new dimension to the playing experience, doesn't it? As for bouldering-inspired tunes, I've been listening to "Vertical Lullaby" - it's a soothing piano piece that captures the calm before the climb. You should give it a listen! 🎹🧗‍♀️ 

Also, I recently watched an Italian film about sustainability and how it intersects with rock climbing. It's called "The Green Climber." It highlights how climbers are embracing eco-friendly practices and working to preserve the climbing areas. Thought you might find it interesting, given our past conversations on climate change. 🌳🧗‍♂️🍃

By the way, have you found any new F1-inspired tunes to play on the Arp recently? I reckon blending those two interests could result in some fascinating musical creations. 🏎️🎶 Cheers, Mary. ##
